      "end": 6.34,
      "text": "This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.34,
      "end": 12.8,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org, recorded by Vicki Barber.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.92,
      "end": 21.24,
      "text": "Asop's Fables, the old woman and the wine jar. An old woman picked up an empty wine",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 21.24,
      "end": 27.22,
      "text": "jar which had once contained a rare and costly wine and which still retained some traces",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 27.22,
      "end": 33.08,
      "text": "of its exquisite bouquet. She raised it to her nose and sniffed at it again and again.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 33.84,
      "end": 41.06,
      "text": "Ah, she cried. How delicious must have been the liquid which has left behind so ravishing a smell.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 42.4,
      "end": 45.34,
      "text": "The end of the old woman and the wine jar.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
